SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: TWO CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICIES EXIST FOR NATIONAL CHURCH RESIDENCES. ONE POLICY IS A GENERAL STAFF POLICY, PUBLISHED IN THE EMPLOYEE INFORMATION GUIDE. THE SECOND POLICY APPLIES TO NATIONAL CHURCH RESIDENCES AND ITS AFFILIATES' OFFICERS, DIRECTORS, AND MEMBERS OF COMMITTEES COMPOSED PRIMARILY OF DIRECTORS AND OFFICERS. THE POLICY FOR OFFICERS AND DIRECTORS IS REVIEWED REGULARLY BY THE BOARD, AND OFFICERS AND DIRECTORS REVIEW AND SIGN AN ATTESTATION RELATED TO THE POLICY ANNUALLY AND ARE REQUIRED TO DISCLOSE ANY POTENTIAL CONFLICTS. THE POLICY CONTAINS A PROCESS FOR REPORTING CONFLICTS, DETERMINING WHETHER A CONFLICT EXISTS, AND APPROPRIATE PROCEDURES FOR ADDRESSING CONFLICTS.
